470 /* basic concepts at http://!<en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queue_(abstract_data_type)
471 * our high-performance queue uses double-buffered fixed memory arrays
472 * it does NOT use dynamically linked lists to reduce ptr overhead
473 * if overflow occurs it either overwrites oldest data or resizes the queue
474 * this depends on the 'resize' flag, if true then overflow will only occur
475 * when memory is capped by the apps total allocatable RAM.
476 * npRealloc() is called to resize, it uses runtime optimized memory pools
477 * in certain cases there is no data copy cost as the memory pool
478 * may already be configured with additional free space at end of the array
479 * A & B buffers are sequentially re-allocated over two program synce cycles
480 * avoids data copy by syncing the resize to the AB swap when the que is clear
481 */
